Subject: Request for Mech/Fire/Hyd Fee Proposal - Beachfit/Slow House Bondi

 

Hi Felix,

 

Hope you're well. 

 

We're working on a fitout for a gym, Beachfit, and a wellness centre, Slow
House, for a client in Bondi and we need to engage a consultant for
mechanical, fire and hydraulics.

 

Beachfit, the gym, is going into the Pacific Building, level 1/180 Campbell
Pde, Bond Beach, NSW 2026 - it is currently a real estate agency office (the
Agency). Lease plan attached. Also attached is the draft plan layout (SK02
NO EQUIPMENT) - equipment is to come based on the supplier's layout. We are
attempting to retain as much of the existing fitout and services as possible
however we do need to add 3 new showers to the rear area which will require
mechanical extract and hydraulic work. 

 

Slow house is a wellness centre going into the Pacific Building, level
B1/180 Campbell Parade, Bondi Beach NSW 2026. The tenancy is currently
Speedo Fitness Club. It currently has a 23m pool, treatment rooms, bathrooms
and gym equipment. We plan to break the pool up into 3 smaller pools - a
larger spa, a cold plunge and a salt pool. We are adding off the shelf
infrared saunas with new showers, treatment rooms, a communal traditional
sauna and steam room. Again where possible we are going to retain the
existing services however we will need to re-rout ductwork and add extract
from showers and potentially the traditional sauna? 

  

We want to have these drawings for our CDC in the first week of Feb. Can you
provide a fee proposal for these 2 projects. Do you need any additional
information to provide this quote? 

 

Let us know if you have any questions.

 

Many thanks,

Anne

 

 


   

Anne Warren
